Zeus is an autonomous AI assistant written in Rust with persistent memory,
8 core tools, unified LLM provider support (11 providers including Anthropic,
OpenAI, Ollama, and more), multi-channel chat (Telegram, Discord, Slack,
Email, Matrix, and more), cognitive engine, security sandboxing, and a REST
API with 105+ endpoints.

Features:
  - File-based and SQLite-backed memory with FTS5 and vector search
  - 8 core tools: read/write/edit files, list dirs, shell, web fetch, spawn, message
  - TUI with 10 screens, REST API with WebSocket streaming
  - Cognitive engine with intent recognition and learning
  - Security sandbox with command filtering and approval system
  - Session management with replay, branching, and audit trails
  - Cross-session pattern recognition and proactive memory retrieval
